args:
A North Grastaean nursery rhyme resounds
across the Halidom. Having heard Aeleen
singing, Verica and other northerners are
excited by the tale of the faerie in the lyrics.
But that night, Verica has an ominous dream
portending a threat approaching from the north.
A few days prior to the clash between the prince's\nNew Alberian Army and the Dyrenell Army led by\nLeonidas and Chelle...
Deep within the quiet, quiet wood\nPlaying hide-and-seek,\nA lone faerie stood...
Sing it again, sing it agaaain!
Again? But you promised to go home\nif I sung it for you last time!
You mustn't trouble Aeleen so,\nas she's quite busy getting ready.
Getting ready for what? ...Oh.\nYou mean more fighting, huh?
Yes, but you've no need to worry yourself.\nOur brave prince will protect this land.
We'll just need you to stay with your mom\nand dad for a bit and hide in a safe place.
Okay. But when the fighting's over,\nI'm gonna come play here again!\nStay safe, everybody! Byeeeee!
Thanks for the save. I feel like we\nwere verging on tantrum territory.
I understand why she didn't want to leave.\nYour song was simply wonderful.
It's a lullaby from North Grastaea, yes?
That's right! Are you from the north as\nwell, Verica? I can't see how you'd\nknow of it otherwise.
I'm not, but I heard it there during my\ntravels as a fortune teller.
I felt someone talking to my inner child\nand came running. Was that you, Aeleen?
It's quite the enchanting voice you've got.\nI totally lost myself in your shanty!
Ack! I can't believe everyone in the\nHalidom heard me singing...
Reminding me of my hometown is nothing\nto be ashamed of! Heck, it makes me\nwonder if I'll ever be able to go back...
Of course you will! Just keep your eye\non the horizon and it'll all work out.
I suppose you're right. Still, it was nice\nto hear the song. I haven't thought about\nfaeries in so long...
Yar, they're more of a northern thing.\n...Well, except for Notte. I wonder if\nshe's from the north or something?
As I understand it, she is a childhood\nfriend of the prince, so I suspect not.
In that case, we oughta invite 'em both\nup to North Grastaea sometime!
I'm sure they would enjoy it.
Danger came for the prince.\nIt came from the north.
...A threat from the north, was it?
That is what my dream portended, yes.\nAnd as such signs often come true,\nI felt the need to warn you at once.
Oh man, that sounds bad. Is there some\nbig enemy or whatever on the way here?\nIs {player_name} gonna be okay?
I'm afraid I can't say for certain.\nIn my dream, all I saw was the\nprince, alone.
If I were to attempt to divine it,\nI would say that you will be made\nto face yourself.
Do you mean a ＂face my doubts and\nweaknesses＂ kind of thing...?
Hmm. Well, thank you for letting me know.\nBut rest assured, I will overcome any\nobstacle that stands in my way.
I can do no less for the sake of my\nallies and the people of New Alberia.
And I'LL totes be at your side\ncheerin' you on like a madwoman!
